                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2">
                        <p>- Decorated quire marks in the upper left corner of the first leaf of quires II-VIII (on the last leaf in quire I)</p>
                        <p>- Daily readings indicated by the names of the days of the week written in the top margin of fols. <locus target="#3r #16r #19v #33v #37v #48r #60v #69v"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- Coloured threads inserted in the edges of fols. <locus target="#6 #12 #16 #19 #33 #36 #48 #60 #69"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>- Fine dichromic (red and black) ornamental band on fol. <locus target="#3r"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- A small design of cross in the top margin of fol. <locus target="#3r"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- Recent miniatures unrelated to the text on fols. <locus target="#76r #77r #78r #79r"/>and <locus target="#80r"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>Fol. <locus target="#3r"/>:  ብስራተ፡አብ፡ትሩፍ፡ረድዕ፡ ተናጋሪ፡በመለኮት፡ዮሐንስ፡ወልደ፡ዘብዴዎስ፡ፍቁረ፡እግዚእነ፡ኢየሱስ፡ክርስቶስ፡፩እም፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ የሃሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ግብሩ፡ ገብረ፡ ኪዳን፡ ለዓለመ፡ዓለመ፡አሜን፨ቀዳሚሁ᎒ቃል፡ውእቱ፨ወውእቱ፡ቃል፡…</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>Ethiopian binding. Two wooden boards.</p>
                           <p>Two pairs of sewing stations. </p>
                           <p>A folded piece of unruled parchment (ca. <locus target="#20"/>.<locus target="#4"/>x <locus target="#8"/>cm) with writing is attached between the front board and the text block at the upper and bottom sewing stations. </p>
                           <p>Kept in the traditional two part slip-case.</p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
